          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                                        <date>Nov 3 of 54</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Friend—</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">I take<lb/> great Pleasure in informing you,<lb/>
                                        that after many Runs, Exertions and<lb/> all other numerous
                                        little difficulties<lb/> attendant upon collecting from men
                                        who<lb/> are opposed to the Idea “to pay up,” that<lb/> I
                                        have succeeded in collecting to-day<lb/> $24— from
                                                  <persName>R. Schoya</persName> for 8 years<lb/>
                                        subscription to the Occident; for this I<lb/> ask some
                                        little Credit from you, as I<lb/> do not believe any one
                                        else could have<lb/> pumped it out of him, acknowledge<lb/>
                                        the Receipt thereof— I would indeed<lb/> like very much to
                                        send you some money,<lb/> but your account now stands yet
                                        about<lb/> $20— overdrawn, as last time I remitted<lb/> much
                                        beyond the funds I <sic>haad</sic> on hand<lb/> for you;
                                        besides I did not yet succeed<lb/> in collecting the
                                        Sunday-School Books Bill.<lb/> To-day I have also collected
                                        from <persName>Mr<lb/> Henry Seligman</persName> $11.86/100
                                        for advertising<lb/> in the Occident, all of which I have
                                        taken<lb/> in for you, I have placed to your Credit;</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>and you will acknowledge also Receipt for<lb/> the latter amt. I
                                        have paid <persName>Spat &amp; Ten-<lb/>-house</persName>
                                        $23 35/100 for Freight &amp;c for the<lb/> sunday school
                                        Books what in also another<lb/> Item to help to
                                        overdraw.</p>
                              <p>Enclosed I hand you an article which I<lb/> cut out from the
                                        “Herald” of this city of<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. Qo</persName>, which may perhaps be of
                                        some<lb/> service to you in as much as it may<lb/> throw
                                        some further light in what<lb/> is hitherto known of the
                                        Jews in <placeName>China</placeName>;<lb/> I have no Doubt,
                                        that Jews exist in<lb/>
                                        <placeName>China</placeName>.</p>
                              <p>I regret exceedingly, that I cannot<lb/> this time inform you of
                                        something in-<lb/>-teresting for the Occident.</p>
                              <p>In conclusion I beg you to accept<lb/> my best wishes for your
                                        welfare &amp;<lb/> Prosperity</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">whilst I Remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">your true friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Cauffman H Meyer</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
